        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Thessalonians 1:3",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ff., while resembling that of the First Epistle, has a special character and fitness of its own. The Apostle dwells (1) on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the signal growth",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the Thessalonian Church ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in faith and love",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Thessalonians 1:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; (1) on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "his own boasting over their faith and patience",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to other Churches, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Thessalonians 1:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and (3) on the token he sees in this of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "God’s righteous judgement",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as between them and their oppressors, which is to take effect at the approaching advent of Christ, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "2 Thessalonians 1:5-10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Thessalonians 1:5-10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This third ground of thanksgiving assumes so much prominence in the Epistle, that it will be convenient to make it the subject of a distinct Section.",
        "children": []
